meanings.definition: To push out or force out
meanings.sent1: She outpushes the door to open it.
meanings.sent2: He outpushes the heavy box across the room.
meanings.sent3: The little robot outpushes the big robot in the race.
meanings.sent4: His determination outpushes any obstacles in his way.
meanings.sent5: The wind outpushes the clouds, revealing the bright sun.

meanings.definition: The act of pushing out or forcing out
meanings.sent1: The outpushes of the crowd made it hard to move forward.
meanings.sent2: The outpushes of air from the fan kept the room cool.
meanings.sent3: The outpushes of laughter filled the room with joy.
meanings.sent4: The outpushes of water from the fountain created a beautiful display.
meanings.sent5: The outpushes of energy from the team led to their victory.
